If I setup a StaticModel before attaching to a node, it will crash, for example:

```
auto mushroomObject = new StaticModel(context_);
mushroomObject->SetModel(cache->GetResource<Model>("Models/Mushroom.mdl"));
mushroomObject->SetMaterial(cache->GetResource<Material>("Materials/Mushroom.xml"));
mushroomNode->AddComponent(mushroomObject, 0, CreateMode::REPLICATED);
```

If I add it before I do SetModel\SetMaterial, it works fine:

```
auto mushroomObject = new StaticModel(context_);
mushroomNode->AddComponent(mushroomObject, 0, CreateMode::REPLICATED); 
mushroomObject->SetModel(cache->GetResource<Model>("Models/Mushroom.mdl"));
mushroomObject->SetMaterial(cache->GetResource<Material>("Materials/Mushroom.xml"));
```

or if I use CreateComponent or GetOrCreateComponent - also works fine!

```
auto mushroomObject = mushroomNode.CreateComponent<StaticModel>(context_);
mushroomObject->SetModel(cache->GetResource<Model>("Models/Mushroom.mdl"));
mushroomObject->SetMaterial(cache->GetResource<Material>("Materials/Mushroom.xml"));
```

